snippet.textDisplay:
Yeah i do believe crush are an ideal of what you see of a certain aspect that you like on someone.

You have a crush not because you like for who they are but for what you like, it's only on the surface level. But is it wrong to work your magic on to your crush. No, because then became step 2, getting to know them better. This step should've been the decision whether to be friends or to go on with the relationship or to leave it.

I have a crush on someone right now, but at the same time i do know her better that if we were to continue with our relationship, it just won't go further than a friend or lasted long if we were a couple.

I have friends saying that i don't know that will happen unless I've tried. well the thing is, I've known her for like 3 years now and what i understand is that her worldview is different than mine. Sure we both have the same hobby and passion but there are certain criteria that just didn't sit well with me or with her. Maybe someday in the future, i don't know. For now i like being friends with her and somehow in the future if we work. Then, we works.
